#eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Around 5,000 people were arrested in connection with the 2021 July arrests but, most of the cases were not prosecuted or even withdrawn. Cabinet's security cluster says 19 cases are still being investigated, with 8 people to be arrested for incitement. Phoenix in KZN was one of the communities torn apart by the 2021 July unrests. It's alleged around 35 people died in the township. Cabinet's security cluster says 31 people have been arrested for attempted murder.  #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  Meanwhile, law enforcement agencies are still investigating about 120 cases. At the same time, Police Minister Bheki Cele says they've increased public order policing capacity since last year's violent unrest in July. He says this has helped police quash similar acts of violence. Watch the video above for more details.